# WiamLight project context

Persistent facts that survive across sessions. Read this first, then read `docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md` for current task state and update it as work progresses.

## Working memory protocol

1. At the start of every session, read `docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md`.
2. After every meaningful decision, blocker, or completed step, append/update the relevant section there.
3. Treat that file as the single source of truth for "what are we currently doing and why".

## Repo layout

- Repo root: `C:\WiamLight` (Windows host, PowerShell shell — quote paths, prefer `curl.exe` over `curl`).
- Backend: `webapp/` (Flask) → Render service custom domain **`https://episio.wiamlabs.com`** (NOT `wiamapp.com` — that host is a separate workers marketplace product).
- Video CDN (Cloudflare R2 public media): **`https://video.episio.wiamlabs.com`** (`CLOUDFLARE_R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL`). This is storage/CDN only — not the Flask API.
- DB is Postgres via `DATABASE_URL` (server-side only). **Production host = Supabase Postgres** (project `evwxgyiadhdsorqcpptc`) per Render env; **Neon is the legacy backup**.
- Mobile: `WiamAppMobile/` — Expo Episio app; API `https://episio.wiamlabs.com/api/v1`.
- Mobile app 2: `WiamVoxMobile/` — Expo app, package `com.wiamlabs.wiamvox`, scheme `wiamvox`.
- QA pipeline: `.github/workflows/qa-enterprise-ceo-rest-mode.yml` — cost-engineered for the 2000-min/month GitHub Actions free tier (every-2h cron, 3 jobs total). Do NOT add jobs without budgeting minutes first.
- Bot: `scripts/qa/comprehensive_bot.py` (38-probe schedule-only QA bot).

## Build & release tooling

- Mobile builds use **EAS Build** (cloud, not local). Invoke with `npx eas-cli ...` (already cached). Production builds: `eas build --profile production --platform android|ios`.
- Mobile Play Store flow is documented in `WiamAppMobile/docs/PLAY_RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md`. Don't duplicate that checklist; track progress against it in `docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md`.
- EAS build commands and local dev setup: `WiamAppMobile/docs/EXPO_BUILD.md`.

## Conventions

- Don't break the QA workflow's free-tier budget (~1640m/month current, ~360m headroom). New scheduled jobs cost ~30 × runs/day minutes/month.
- **WiamEpisio production API:** `https://episio.wiamlabs.com/api/v1` (`EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` in eas.json). Never point Episio at `wiamapp.com`.
- **Email roles:** `SUPPORT_EMAIL` (default `support@wiamapp.com`) = users / public policy / Play. `COMPANY_EMAIL` (default `labs@wiamapp.com`) = team accounts, QA dashboards, internal ops. Override via env on Render if needed.
- **Deploy (Episio Flask on Render):** GitHub repo **`WiamLabs/WiamEpisio`** (renamed from WiamApp; Old-WiamApp archived). Branches `episio-flask-deploy` / `master` @ latest ship. Auto-deploy may be OFF — verify Render Git connection points at `WiamEpisio` and use **Manual Deploy** if needed. Probe live with `https://episio.wiamlabs.com/health` and `/api/v1/episio/media-specs` — never `wiamapp.com`.
